About
Amsterdam's murky past comes to life at the Amsterdam Dungeon * walk through Amsterdam’s sinister past * 500 years of history brought to you in about 80 minutes * meet our witch hunter, soul merchant and many other mouth breathers * go deep into the dungeon with (max) 29 other sinners * you are part of the show (or push another victim forward) * Scary True Stories and 'orrible Actors * English spoken… but also available in Dutch…. If you want to brag! * 10 years or younger? We wouldn’t do it, but that’s just an advise * Don’t tell anyone, but you can leave if you can’t take it anymore

The area

Address
Neighborhood: Centrum
Amsterdam’s buzzing hub, with its sprawling network of tram rails and a seemingly constant flow of tourists and commuters, yields convenient access to some of the best sightseeing, shopping, and street life in Europe. Closest at hand are the Royal Palace, the quaint shops of Haalremmerdijk, the pedestrianized zones Kalverstraat and Dam Square with popular neighborhoods such as the Red Light District, and the Canal Ring hardly more than a moment’s stroll away. With the well-connected Centraal Station as Centrum’s base, it's easy to travel farther afield via one of the city’s iconic trams.
How to get there
  • Nieuwmarkt • 9 min walk
  • Waterlooplein • 10 min walk

    A must if you are in Amsterdam
    It is a must if you are in Amsterdam. It is not scary at all if you enter with the mindset that it is a safe experience and nothing will happen to you. It is a funny, unexpecetd and really amazing experience. There are well prepared actors who are dressed according to the show and are very good at what they do. You pass from one room to another and live a different advenure in every room. It is an interactive experience where the public(visitors) are included, and is better enjoyed if everyone plays the part according to instructions they give you. The only bad thing is that it is not allowed to take photos or videos of your own inside, but at the entrance they take some funny pictures of you that you can purchase at the end of the experience.

Do you offer a free carer admission ticket for disabled visitors paying full price admission?
Written April 12, 2019
Andy Naarden
35 contributions
As far as I know they don't! Also I'd like to point out that the Dungeon is not very "disabled friendly" as you move from room to room in a very old typical Amsterdam building with unexpected steps, very narrow passages and it's very very dark everywhere. It's certainly not wheel chair accessible.. But to make sure it's accessible to your disabled visitor, you might want to contact them directly. I found their contact details for you: email: info@theamsterdamdungeon.nl phone: +31 20 530 8500 Good luck and if you do go, I'm sure you'll have a great time! Kind regards, Andy
